climbs.name: Stargazer
climbs.fa: Brent Webster, Troy Pascoe, Leslie Gobel

content.description: Crux is at the bottom in the first 2 clips, while climbing over a small bulge. After that the route becomes more slabby and eventually develops larger chunky holds up to the anchor on the right.
content.location: Shorter climb on the upper right side of Middle Tier. Follow the fixed ropes up and to the right, where there is a dirt covered ledge below the start.

content.description: In between Honey Dipped and Hashtag Selfie is a fifth route up here. Bouldery moves down low lead to decent small holds the rest of the way. Â Slightly runout from the last bolt to the anchors.
Superfun climbing for the grade, climb the face and arete on good jugs. Finish up easy runout slab to the anchors on the right of the Local Ledge.
content.location: After climbing the approach waterfall to the middle tier, Spiderkids is the first climb on the Right side of the canyon.

content.description: Climb up easy ground then bust a boulder problem at the first bolt, continue up fun technical face, Sooo sweet its honey dipped....
content.location: left route on the ledge, left of the big horn.

climbs.name: Hashtag Selfie
climbs.fa: Josh Fraiser, Sam Schmetzer, Aaron Lawrence

content.description: More like #super stoked because that's how you are going to feel getting to the chains on this one. Another awesome route bolted by the man himself, Brent Webster, thanks Brentle! Left of honey dipped, take the big ramp to the first bolt. Sweet left hand leaner jugs through the 2nd bolt, hang a sharp right down the little ledge after the 3rd bolt, and then to the thin slabby section up to the intimidating looking roof.
content.location: After you climb the 1st section of the waterfall take the ledge to the right, begin left of honey dipped up the slabby ramp.

content.description: fun climbing to a roof in a left facing dihedral. continue up steep rock.
content.location: right route on the ledge, right side of the canyon.

content.description: A very fun route on good holds, a fun crux climbing out of the dihedral. Thank Brent for all the time spent on this route.
content.location: The middle line on the east side belay ledge, right above "Just the Tip" Can be done is one long 110' pitch.
